<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-06-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-06-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="1000" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1000">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/31.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-06T15:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1913—3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>240. Your June 3. You may instruct consuls to render, whenever it appears
                            to them to be necessary, such informal good offices as may be possible,
                            and as the local authorities may permit to be exercised, to Chinese
                            resident in Mexico.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>